# 1. What is your favourite food?

My favourite food is probably hot pot, especially Sichuan-style hot pot. I really enjoy it because it’s not just about the taste, but also the atmosphere. In China, hot pot is usually eaten with friends or family, so it feels very social and relaxing. I love spicy food, and I enjoy choosing different ingredients like beef, mushrooms and seafood. Whenever I feel stressed from studying, having hot pot with friends is one of the best ways for me to unwind.

### 中文翻译：

我最喜欢的食物应该是火锅，尤其是四川火锅。我喜欢它不仅因为味道好，还因为它的氛围感。在中国，火锅通常是和朋友或家人一起吃的，所以会让人感觉很轻松、很有社交感。我很喜欢吃辣，也很享受挑选不同食材，比如牛肉、蘑菇和海鲜。每当我学习压力很大的时候，和朋友一起吃火锅就是我最喜欢的放松方式之一。

---

# 2. What kind of food did you like when you were young?

When I was a child, I was really into fast food and snacks, especially fried chicken, hamburgers and potato chips. At that age, I paid much more attention to taste rather than nutrition. I remember I used to beg my parents to take me to fast-food restaurants on weekends. However, as I’ve grown older, my eating habits have changed quite a bit. Now I prefer healthier and more balanced meals because I realize diet can strongly affect both physical health and energy levels.

### 中文翻译：

小时候，我特别喜欢快餐和零食，尤其是炸鸡、汉堡和薯片。那个年纪的我更在意味道，而不是营养。我记得以前总会求父母周末带我去快餐店。不过随着年龄增长，我的饮食习惯变化挺大的。现在我更喜欢健康、均衡的食物，因为我意识到饮食会对身体状态和精力产生很大影响。

---

# 3. Do you eat different foods at different times of the year?

Yes, definitely. I think my eating habits change quite a lot depending on the season. For example, during winter, I usually prefer hot and spicy food like hot pot or noodles because they help me feel warm. In contrast, during summer, I tend to eat lighter food such as fruit, salads or cold noodles since heavy meals can make people feel uncomfortable in hot weather. Seasonal food is also quite common in China, so people naturally adjust their diets throughout the year.

### 中文翻译：

当然会。我觉得自己的饮食习惯会随着季节变化而有很大不同。比如冬天的时候，我通常更喜欢火锅或者面条这种热腾腾、偏辣的食物，因为它们会让人感觉暖和。而到了夏天，我则更倾向于吃水果、沙拉或者凉面这种比较清淡的食物，因为天气太热时，油腻食物会让人不舒服。在中国，季节性饮食本来就很常见，所以人们通常会随着一年四季调整自己的饮食。
